Ok thanks for the output, which is really, really strange, as your
monitor should support DDC/CI, but doesn't answer to standard commands.

On the nVidia card (or the S3 card if you know the name of the
framebuffer driver), could you try to load rivafb (or ???fb) and i2c-dev
kernel modules, then run "i2cdetect -l" and "i2cdetect #" (where # is
your graphics card I2C bus number). (just in case i2cdetect is in
lm_sensors package).

Thanks,

Best regards,

Nicolas



