On Mon, Jun 19, 2006 at 07:45:52PM +0200, Nicolas Boichat wrote:

> Sorry for the delay (I've been really really busy), thanks for the
> output. I added the monitor to the database. It would be nice if you
> could play with the 0x14 value (colorpreset), and give me the meaning of
> these values : 0x01, 0x02, 0x05, 0x08, 0x0B.
 
Here it is:
     1 - sRGB
     2 - Original color
     5 - 6500K
     8 - 9300K
    11 - User Define
  
When you select "User Define" in monitor menu, sliders for R,G,B adjusting 
appeared.
 
