Hello.=20

I have checked cvs with the updated database and used the GUI with this=20
monitor. It works and is very handy, thank you. These are a couple of minor=
=20
bugs I found:

1) The entry for 9300k color is missing in gddccontrol. I inserted a line=
=20=20
<value id=3D"9300k"  value=3D"0x8"/>  in the "colorpreset" section of SYNlc=
d.xml=20

2) Restoring factory defaults with gddccontrol gives "Error while getting=20
value: Backlight", while the main window shows "Refreshing controls values=
=20
(0%)...". After the error window is closed, the refresh completes well and=
=20
the main window shows a Backlight value of 0 (the actual is 100, default fo=
r=20
preset High).


-) Since I didn't report the gamma values this one is my fault: it is a=20
little difficult to deal with the Gamma slider because most of its position=
s=20
establish the default gamma 120. Below is the relationship between the=20
meaningful values of the monitor's OSD, tha gamma control and gddccontrol:

-----------------------------------------------
Monitor's OSD:    1.8    2.0   2.2   2.4   2.6   # greater is darker
Monitor's 0x72:    80    100   120   140   160   # any other value writes 1=
20
gddccontrol %: |=B7=B7=B750=B7=B7=B7=B762.5=B7=B7=B775=B7=B787.5=B7=B7=B710=
0|  # '=B7' results in 120
-----------------------------------------------

That is, the SDM-S205F/K accepts only five gamma values and defaults to 120=
 in=20
any other case. Then the user gets the default most of times unless (s)he s=
ets=20
positions very close to those percentages in the slider, which is a bit=20
tricky and difficult to remember (the Profile manager comes handy here).=20
While this is not a bug on your side it would be better to have a 5-steps=20
slider or radio buttons if possible.


Regards, and good luck with your exams.

lardhan




