Hello,

You don't really need to take ddccontrol support into account before
buying one of these monitors:
You can buy NEC without any problem, the monitors you plan to buy are
not supported in the database yet, but I have good contacts with NEC, so
it won't be a problem to add one of these monitors.
You can also buy Samsung, we have strong support for these monitors,
thanks to the some users who gave very complete informations.

Anyway, even if you buy a monitor of whatever other brand, maybe not
supported by ddccontrol, as long as the monitor supports DDC/CI (and is
not too buggy), you will at least be able to control basic parameters
like brightness and contrast.

Best regards,

Nicolas

