Hello,

Scott Storck wrote:
> Hello,
>
> I'm trying to get ddccontrol working with my PC running SLED10.
> I've built and installed the software myself.
> On another PC my build works fine using the same monitor. :D
>
> The PC which isn't working is a Dell Optiplex GX620.
> The monitor being used is a Dell 1707FP.
>
> As far as I can see this PC has an Intel 945G for the graphics.
> I looked in the documentation from ddccontrol, and I saw that a 945G
> uses PCI access to the DDC.
> Which as far as I can see, needs no special kernel modules loaded.
>
> Can anybody help me with this?
> Output from ddccontrol below.
>   
Is the other computer running the same hardware and software ? If they
are, the problem is probably not in ddccontrol.

You could try to compile intelfb in your kernel (and i2c-dev), and see
if it works (follow the instructions for nVidia or ATI, but choose Intel
FB instead of ATI or nVidia FB).

Best regards,

Nicolas


