Hi,
I tried latest db (20061014) with Samsung SyncMaster 971P and analog cord
(just a coincidence, in fact). Ddcontrol didn't find monitor in db therefore
I attach output of
$ LANG= LC_ALL= ./ddccontrol -p -c -d samsung_SM971P_analog.txt

I also tried to use SAM0248 as required SAM0247
and results are fine (brightness, contrast and color temperature works). So
it's a success story. ;)

I had other issues while building. It may be my distro issue, but... I was
building with static libpci.a and configure said I don't have pci-utils. I
don't know much about autotools (not even close to much :) ) but I found
that simple test:
#v+
#include <pci/pci.h>

int main(void) {
    pci_alloc();
    return 0;
}
#v-
didn't compile with `gcc -o a -lpci -lz a.c` (undefined reference to
`pci_alloc'). But it's good with `gcc -o a a.c -lpci -lz` (gcc 3.4.5). Also
zlib is required (-lz) at link time.

So I made simple patch for configure.ac (disables real test for pci_alloc
and adds zlib dependency) - attached.

Then building was fine. So, if anyone has problems with configure not
finding pci_alloc may try this. Success story after all.

Thanks for fine work.
Cheers,
Lukasz Krotowski

